    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "html": "เ-ย Notice that the [-um] and [-ai] sounds can be made by just one vowel, or they can be combinations of “ -ั ” and ม or ย. Complete tone summary The “String Theory” that we have learnt in this book are the essential rules for tone production, and for 99% of words you will not need to remember anything else but those. However, if you’re a perfectionist and want to know all there is to know about tone rules, including those that are hardly used ones, here are all the possible combinations. 64 no mark"
